Package: rsymbolic2
Type: Package
Title: Symbolic Regression via Genetic Programming
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Toshihiro", "Iguchi", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "toshihiro.iguchi.mail@gmail.com")
Description: Discovers mathematical expressions that fit data using a
    steady-state genetic programming algorithm with Levenberg-Marquardt
    constant optimization. The search engine is implemented in C++ and
    exposed through a single R function. The default configuration and
    search behaviour are matched to the documented defaults of 'PySR'
    (Cranmer, 2023, <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2305.01582>) and
    'SymbolicRegression.jl'; this
    package is an independent re-implementation and is not affiliated with
    or endorsed by those projects. See the NOTICE file for attribution.
License: Apache License 2.0
Encoding: UTF-8
URL: https://github.com/ToshihiroIguchi/rsymbolic2
BugReports: https://github.com/ToshihiroIguchi/rsymbolic2/issues
Depends: R (>= 4.2.0)
LinkingTo: cpp11
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0), ggplot2
Config/testthat/edition: 3
RoxygenNote: 8.0.0
